    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Christian Yelich** (70.52) and **Trea Turner** (70.10) anchor the Zurich Zebras as our most potent options. **Christian Yelich** benefits significantly from a favorable dynamic platoon advantage against Zack Littell, while **Trea Turner** remains an essential start despite facing a high-caliber arm in Gallen, as his lead-off spot and elite efficiency baseline sustain his high floor. **Colt Keith** (68.60) is another highlight; he faces Sandy Alcantara, but the combination of a positive park factor and a 97% SB-permissive environment created by the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery makes him a high-upside play for our stolen base-starved categories. Similarly, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.03) gains significant value today due to favorable winds, which help offset the difficulty of facing Bubba Chandler.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Victor Scott II** (57.13). While his elite sprint speed is exactly the type of profile we prioritize, his projected floor was dampened by a bottom-of-the-order assignment, making him less efficient than **Josh Smith** (62.13), whose matchup against Roki Sasaki allows for a massive 19% SP skill bonus that nudges him over the threshold. We are also monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Caleb Durbin**, **Chase Meidroth**, and **Yordan Alvarez**. **Yordan Alvarez** (58.58) carries the highest risk today; while his BvP history and power profile are strong, his score is suppressed by a brutal matchup against Logan Gilbert (2.86 xERA). If the confirmed lineups shift our expected order for **Caleb Durbin** or **Chase Meidroth** downward, we may see their scores fluctuate, but for now, they are locked into high-efficiency roles.",
